function bitmap = DrawText2Bitmap(textString, textRect, textSize, fontName, justification)% bitmap = DrawText2Bitmap(textString, textRect, textSize, fontName, justification)%	%	Draws the specified text into an offscreen GWorld (8-bit color) and%	copies the bitmap from that GWorld into 'bitmap'.  The text should be%	in a row vector- the Mac toolbox routine TextBox (which does the%	drawing) will do word-wrap and clip the bottom (if necessary) to make%	the text fit into textRect.%	%	If you don't need word-wrap, use DrawTextLine2Bitmap- it gives you the%	text all on one line in a rect just big enough.%	%%   textString = matlab string (row vector of chars)%   textRect = [top left right bottom]%   textSize = font size in points (default = 12)%   fontName = matlab string specifying font name- try 'geneva' (default),%					'courier', 'new york', 'monaco', etc.%   justification = -1 for right, 0 for left (default), 1 for center%%